article.headline: SMU 56, Alabama St. 51
article.story: DALLAS -- Paul McCoy scored 18 points to lead SMU past Alabama St. 56-51 on Saturday night. SMU (2-1) trailed 40-39 midway through the second half before McCoy scored seven points in a 16-5 run. McCoy hit a 3-pointer and Bamba Fall added a free throw to put the Mustangs ahead 56-46 with 2:18 left. Rashad Provitt scored 13 points and Andrew Hayles added 10 for Alabama St. (0-3), who hit only 9-of-33 shots in the second half. Fall had 12 points and tied a career-high with 12 rebounds.
